a strong earthquake struck central and northern 
japan on sunday night shaking tall buildings and rattling windows 
in downtown tokyo no damage or injuries were immediately reported 
the national police agency said 
the quake which occurred at 928 pm 728 am est measured 
56 on the richter scale and was centered 60 miles north of tokyo in 
the town of utsunomiya the meterological agency said the quake 
shook all of northern honshu japans main island the agency said 
new tokyo international airport in narita 40 miles northeast of 
tokyo closed its main runway to check for damage but opened it 13 
minutes later when no damage was found officials there said 
in the associated press office on the 11th floor of a building in 
central tokyo plate glass windows rattled for about 30 seconds 
clocks wobbled on walls and chairs moved across the floor 
japan is in a very active seismological area and has had major 
earthquakes in the past the most serious one this century occurred 
in 1923 when about 140000 residents of tokyo and neighboring 
yokohama died in a quake and fires 
an earthquake measuring 5 on the richter scale can cause 
considerable damage a temblor measuring 6 on the scale can cause 
severe damage 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
